cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of word features and Bayesian analysis for scientometric analysis, which falls under the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), software development (cs.SD), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The focus on analyzing the proceedings of a specific society also suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). However, based on the content of the abstract, the first five sub-categories listed are the most likely matches.
